ontend simulation and not a live AI agent. No API calls. No fake real-time claims. Use a premium step-by-step timeline, animated workflow path, or tabbed execution viewer. Add related CTAs to Talk to Agent, Blueprint, and Foundry Studio. Mobile and accessibility must be excellent. Run lint and build.\"\n433 |   },\n434 |   {\n435 |     \"id\": \"54-phase3-agent-marketplace-tool\",\n436 |     \"title\": \"Build Build Marketplace interactive catalog\",\n437 |     \"scope\": \"phase3-tool\",\n438 |     \"target\": \"/build/marketplace\",\n439 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n440 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /build/marketplace into a premium interactive agent and accelerator catalog. Do not touch landing page. Use local static data only. Include categories: Knowledge Agents, Operations Agents, Compliance Agents, Customer Experience Agents, Executive Agents, Document Intelligence Agents, Procurement Agents, HR Agents. Add filters by industry, function, maturity stage, and platform fit. Add search. Add comparison drawer allowing up to 3 agent patterns. No pricing, no fake purchasable products, no fake availability. Each card should include use case, where it fits in Garage/Foundry/Factory, related capabilities, and CTA to Sandbox or Talk to Agent. Use carousel, bento grid, tabs, and motion if appropriate. Mobile excellent. Run lint and build.\"\n441 |   },\n442 |   {\n443 |     \"id\": \"55-phase3-foundry-studio-workflow-builder\",\n444 |     \"title\": \"Build Foundry Studio visual workflow builder preview\",\n445 |     \"scope\": \"phase3-tool\",\n446 |     \"target\": \"/build/foundry-studio\",\n447 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n448 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /build/foundry-studio into a premium visual workflow builder preview. Do not touch landing page. This must be frontend-only and not a real builder backend. Create a visual flow where users can select an industry, choose an agent pattern, add workflow stages, add knowledge sources as labels, add human approval points, and see a generated local workflow map. Use deterministic local state. No drag-and-drop dependency unless already installed; use click-to-add modules or simple reorder buttons if needed. Visual modules can include Trigger, Agent Reasoning, Knowledge Graph, Tool Action, Human Review, Governance Check, Output, Control Center Monitoring. Add a polished architecture canvas with SVG/CSS connections. Add CTAs to Proposal Builder and Sandbox. Mobile should degrade gracefully into a stacked workflow. Run lint and build.\"\n449 |   },\n450 |   {\n451 |     \"id\": \"56-phase3-build-hub-unified-experience\",\n452 |     \"title\": \"Upgrade Build With GFF hub as product launcher\",\n453 |     \"scope\": \"phase3-tool\",\n454 |     \"target\": \"/build\",\n455 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n456 |     \"prompt\": \"Upgrade /build into a premium self-service product launcher for all Build With GFF tools. Do not touch landing page. The page should help users understand which tool to use next. Include a hero, enterprise flow: Visitor, AI Assessment, Blueprint, Workshop, Proposal, Contract, Delivery, Operate, Expand. Add tool launcher cards for Talk to Agent, Blueprint Generator, AI Readiness Assessment, ROI Calculator, Sandbox, Proposal Builder, Marketplace, Foundry Studio. Add a decision guide section: If you are exploring use Assessment, if you know the challenge use Talk, if you need a roadmap use Blueprint, if you need economics use ROI, if you need a proposal use Proposal Builder. Add a local 'continue where you left off' panel if local storage state exists. Design must be premium, clear, interactive, and mobile-friendly. Run lint and build.\"\n457 |   },\n458 |   {\n459 |     \"id\": \"57-phase3-local-workspace-continuity\",\n460 |     \"title\": \"Add local workspace continuity across Build tools\",\n461 |     \"scope\": \"phase3-state\",\n462 |     \"target\": \"local workspace continuity\",\n463 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n464 |     \"