n479 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n480 |     \"prompt\": \"Enhance the Command Center with Build With GFF deep actions. Do not touch landing page. Existing Cmd+K/Ctrl+K behavior must remain. Add commands for Start Blueprint, Continue Blueprint if local state exists, Start Assessment, Estimate ROI, Build Proposal, Open Sandbox, Compare Agents, Open Foundry Studio, Clear Local Workspace, Contact Sales, Book Workshop. Keep it frontend-only. Use route navigation and local actions only. Ensure keyboard accessibility, focus trap if modal, escape close, mobile fallback button if needed, and visible focus states. Do not redesign global header unless required. Run lint and build.\"\n481 |   },\n482 |   {\n483 |     \"id\": \"60-phase3-tool-empty-loading-error-states\",\n484 |     \"title\": \"Polish empty loading error and completion states\",\n485 |     \"scope\": \"phase3-ux-polish\",\n486 |     \"target\": \"all Build tools\",\n487 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n488 |     \"prompt\": \"Polish empty states, loading-like transitions, error states, validation states, completion states, and reset states across all Build With GFF tools. Do not touch landing page. Tools: /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /build/sandbox, /build/proposal, /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio. Since everything is frontend-only, use short deterministic transitions only where tasteful. Empty states must explain what the user should do. Validation states must be clear and accessible. Completion states must include next actions. Error states must not be scary or fake backend errors. Use premium microcopy and consistent visuals. Run lint and build.\"\n489 |   },\n490 |   {\n491 |     \"id\": \"61-phase3-mobile-pass-build-tools\",\n492 |     \"title\": \"Mobile UX pass for Build With GFF tools\",\n493 |     \"scope\": \"phase3-mobile-qa\",\n494 |     \"target\": \"Build tool pages\",\n495 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n496 |     \"prompt\": \"Perform a mobile UX pass for all Build With GFF tools. Do not redesign and do not touch landing page. Check /build, /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /build/sandbox, /build/proposal, /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio. Fix only mobile and responsive issues. Ensure no horizontal overflow, readable text, easy form inputs, large tap targets, stepper usability, accessible carousels/tabs, stacked result panels, simplified diagrams, usable comparison drawer, and workflow builder fallback. Do not add new features. Run lint and build.\"\n497 |   },\n498 |   {\n499 |     \"id\": \"62-phase3-accessibility-pass-build-tools\",\n500 |     \"title\": \"Accessibility pass for Build With GFF tools\",\n501 |     \"scope\": \"phase3-accessibility-qa\",\n502 |     \"target\": \"Build tool pages\",\n503 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n504 |     \"prompt\": \"Perform an accessibility pass for all Build With GFF interactive tools. Do not touch landing page. Check labels, aria attributes where needed, keyboard navigation, focus states, form errors, tab/carousel controls, modal/dialog focus handling, command center deep actions, reduced motion, heading order, semantic sections, color contrast, and button/link semantics. Fix only accessibility issues. Do not redesign. Ensure every tool page has one clear H1 and that result panels are announced/readable. Run lint and build.\"\n505 |   },\n506 |   {\n507 |     \"id\": \"63-phase3-motion-and-interaction-polish\",\n508 |     \"title\": \"Motion and interaction polish for Build tools\",\n509 |     \"scope\": \"phase3-visual-polish\",\n510 |     \"target\": \"Build tool pages\",\n511 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n512 |     \"prompt\": \"Perform a motion and interaction polish pass for Build With GFF tools. Do not touch landing page. Use Framer Motion or motion/react only if already installed. Improve step transitions, hover states, selected option states, result reveals, tab transitions, carousel movement, workflow map reveal, score chart animation, and CTA micro-interactions. Keep motion subtle, expensive, and purposeful. Respect prefers-reduced-motion. Avoid noisy animation, excessive glows, and fake loading. Do not add dependencies. Run lint and build.\"\n513 |   },\n514 |   {\n515 |     \"id\": \"64-phase3-visual-premium-polish-build-tools\",\n516 |     \"title\": \"Premium visual polish for Build tools\",\n517 |     \"scope\": \"phase3-visual-polish\",\n518 |     \"target\": \"Build tool pages\",\n519 |     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n520 |     \"prompt\": \"Perform final premium UI polish only on Build With GFF tools. Do not touch landing page. Make /build and all tool pages feel like a custom 2026 enterprise product suite. Fix generic-looking sections, weak spacing, repetitive cards, clumsy forms, unbalanced layouts, and any UI that feels AI-generated. Add page-specific visual ideas where missing: score ring, architecture diagram, workflow canvas, product preview, executive report panel, carousel, bento grid, tabbed insight panel, comparison drawer, or timeline. Do not add fake data. Do not add dependencies. Preserve the current site theme. Run lint and build.\"","success":true}],"durationMs":2}}
