{"ts":"2026-06-26T23:19:06.109Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing the GFF Integration**\n\nI've got it! Task 59 is all about integrating Build With GFF actions into the Command Center. The key is to enhance functionality without touching the landing page or disrupting the existing Cmd+K/Ctrl+K behavior. I need to add commands for Start Blueprint, but I haven't considered the other deep actions.\n\n\n**Expanding Actionable Commands**\n\nI'm expanding the actionable commands within the command center, ensuring a frontend-only implementation with route navigation and local actions. I've added functionality for \"Start Blueprint,\" \"Continue Blueprint\" (conditional on local state), \"Start Assessment,\" \"Estimate ROI,\" \"Build Proposal,\" \"Open Sandbox,\" and \"Compare Agents\". Keyboard accessibility and a focus trap, if modal, are crucial. I'm also ensuring escape-to-close functionality, a mobile fallback button, and visible focus states, all without redesigning the global header unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n**Verifying Keyboard Accessibility**\n\nI'm now diving deep into `components/CommandCenter.tsx`. I'm specifically verifying the keyboard accessibility, including modal focus trapping to keep the user's tab focus within the modal. I'm also ensuring the escape-to-close functionality, visible focus states, and the correct handling of tab key navigation within the command center are working as expected. I'm keen to ensure no accessibility bugs have slipped through.\n\n\n**Confirming Keyboard Navigation**\n\nI've confirmed keyboard navigation is perfect, intercepting \"Tab\" to cycle through the filtered command list. \"Enter\" executes the selected command. The search input remains active, allowing continuous keyboard interaction. The focus trap within the modal is working exactly as expected, trapping keyboard focus correctly. I am now checking the behavior on the input field itself, since that is the only focusable element that is not a list element.\n\n\n**Refining Focus Behavior**\n\nI'm refining the focus behavior within the command center. I've realized the Tab key never actually moves focus away from the input field, even though the list is empty, and instead cycles the selection with Tab and Shift+Tab, using a custom keyboard handler to avoid browser default focus behavior.\n\n\n**Validating Screen Reader Compatibility**\n\nI'm now validating screen reader compatibility. When the search is empty, arrow keys, Tab, or Enter have no effect, which is the expected behavior. I've confirmed that the escape key still closes the modal, which is good. My focus is now on ensuring proper screen reader interaction with the command palette. I've double checked the list's `role=\"listbox\"`, `aria-label=\"Search results\"`, the command buttons' `role=\"option\"`, and the combobox's `role=\"combobox\"` and WAI-ARIA attributes, and it seems the implementation conforms to the WAI-ARIA Combobox pattern perfectly.\n\n\n"}}
