wser storage, and automatically parses and triggers the state loading.\n* **`app/build/marketplace/page.tsx`**:\n  * Added client-side detection for `?compare=true`. On mount, it sets preloaded default high-value agents into the comparison selection and opens the Comparison Drawer automatically to guide the user's focus.\n\n---\n\n### Validation Done\n1. **Lint and Compilation Check**:\n   * Executed `npm run lint` — returned **0 errors or warnings**.\n2. **Next.js Static Generation / Build Check**:\n   * Executed `npm run build` — compiled successfully in **under 4 seconds** with **0 TS / routing issues**, generating 110 premium static files correctly.\n3. **Accessibility and Guardrail Audit**:\n   * No backend dependencies, credentials, or fake reports were introduced.\n   * Modals trap keyboard focus internally and handle escape hooks correctly.\n   * Responsive layout support remains intact.\n\n---\n\n### Limitations\n* All actions operate under a **frontend-only simulation layer** in standard with GFF AI's phase-3 project requirements. No backend servers, external databases, or AWS integrations are active. All persistence resides cleanly and securely inside the browser's `localStorage` context.\n\nI will now submit the final status and complete the task."}}
